Reasoning: The paper discusses the comparison of spectral efficiency achievable through joint processing of pilot and data symbols with the conventional approach of separate processing. This topic falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The paper also discusses the use of mutual information lower bound, which is a common technique in statistical inference (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of a small number of pilot symbols, which is related to network optimization (cs.NI) and data structures (cs.DS).
